[size=200][b]MothBane[/b][/size]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/flexxall/MothBane/main/mothView.png[/img]

In Harandar, Glowing Moth treasures share the same minimap sparkle as lots of other treasures. That makes it easy to waste time chasing the wrong dot—or miss what you actually wanted. [b]MothBane[/b] keeps those moths readable by swapping Blizzard’s usual treasure ping for something you choose: a clear [b]shadow[/b] overlay or a dedicated [b]moth[/b] icon.

Lightweight, [b]no dependencies[/b], World of Warcraft [b]Retail[/b].

[size=150][b]Why use this?[/b][/size]
[list]
[*] Spot moth treasures [b]without[/b] confusing them with unrelated treasures on the minimap.
[*] Pick the visual that fits how you navigate the zone—shadow or moth icon.
[*] Toggle everything off anytime with [b]Enable MothBane[/b] or [b]/mothbane off[/b] if you want vanilla behaviour back.
[/list]

[size=150][b]Features[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]Two minimap styles[/b] – Replace the default treasure vignette with a [b]shadow[/b] tint or your [b]moth[/b] artwork so moths stand out from other treasure pins.
[*][b]Adjustable icon scale[/b] – Small / Medium / Large so the overlay matches your minimap setup.
[*][b]Minimap launcher[/b] – Optional button on the minimap (hide it and use [b]/mothbane[/b] only if you prefer a clean rim).
[*][b]In-game settings[/b] – Enable/disable, style, scale, and minimap button visibility from one panel.
[/list]

[size=150][b]Slash commands[/b][/size]
[code]/mothbane              Open or close the settings window (handy when the minimap button is hidden).
/mothbane on           Enable MothBane (same as /mothbane 1).
/mothbane off          Disable MothBane (same as /mothbane 0).
[/code]

[size=150][b]Opening the UI[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]Minimap:[/b] Left-click the moth icon for options. [b]Right-click and drag[/b] to move the icon.
[*][b]Slash:[/b] Type [b]/mothbane[/b] to toggle the settings window.
[/list]

[size=150][b]Settings[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]Enable MothBane[/b] – Master on/off for all minimap behaviour.
[*][b]Show minimap button[/b] – Shows or hides the moth launcher on the minimap rim.
[*][b]Replace Blizzard treasure with[/b] – [b]Shadow[/b] or [b]Moth[/b] over each Glowing Moth on the minimap; default is [b]Moth[/b].
[*][b]Icon scale[/b] – [b]Small[/b], [b]Medium[/b], or [b]Large[/b] overlay size.
[/list]

[size=150][b]Installation[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]1.[/b] Download the latest zip from [url=https://www.curseforge.com/wow/addons/mothbane]CurseForge[/url].
[*][b]2.[/b] Extract so the [b]MothBane[/b] folder (with [b]MothBane.toc[/b], [b]MothBane.lua[/b], etc.) sits inside [i]World of Warcraft\_retail_\Interface\AddOns\[/i].
[*][b]3.[/b] Restart WoW or run [b]/reload[/b].
[/list]

[size=150][b]Bugs & suggestions[/b][/size]
Use [b]CurseForge comments[/b] or [url=https://github.com/flexxall/MothBane/issues]GitHub Issues[/url].
